					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>it also is far from a bad dado article. Like, you haven't done any of the things that people tend to when overextending the joke.</p> </blockquote> <p>Hard agree. Even though it follows a relatively standard set-up/punchline format, I like this sort of thing an order of magnitude more than some of the other, more bloated, dado articles. It's a neat anomalous effect with good dialogue and a clear place in-universe; that's enough to get me to upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
